JOHANNESBURG - Hip-hop artists have been celebrating the first-ever permanent Hip-Hop Museum, showing off their moves in Newtown, Johannesburg. Arts and Culture Minister Nathi Mthethwa launched the venue on Thursday. He has urged artists to expand the museum to not only hip-hop but other genres as well. The museum boasts not only about the culture of Hip Hop but also the events that transpired to shape it to the movement that it is today. pic.twitter.com/NwEqBS7orN  pic.twitter.com/5CJ8HBWgGO  The newly refurbished state-of-the-art facility is aimed at preserving the hip-hop culture. Itâ€™s also aimed at driving education and empowerment through workshops. The day was celebrated by not only people in the hip-hop fraternity but also musicians across all genres. The minister has used the launch to not only congratulate the hip-hop fraternity but also to urge creatives to own their crafts.